  "prompt": "Which cold coffee is the best in CCD?",
  "response": "Choosing the best cold coffee at Caf\u00e9 Coffee Day (CCD) can be subjective, as it depends on individual taste preferences. However, some popular cold coffee options at CCD include:\n\n1. **Devil's Own:** This is a rich and creamy cold coffee with chocolate syrup, perfect for those who love a chocolatey twist in their coffee.\n\n2. **Cafe Frappe:** A classic choice, this is a smooth blend of coffee and ice, often topped with whipped cream.\n\n3. **Kaapi Nirvana:** A slightly more intense coffee flavor, this frappe is great for true coffee lovers.\n\n4. **Cold Brew:** For those who prefer a less sweet and more robust coffee flavor, CCD\u2019s cold brew is a refreshing option.\n\nUltimately, the best cold coffee for you will depend on whether you prefer something sweeter, more chocolatey, or more coffee-forward. It might be worth trying a few different options to see which one you enjoy the most!",
